9 (6) If for any reason, any vacancy in the office of mayor or the legislative body is not
10 filled within thirty (30) days after it occurs, the Governor shall promptly fill the
11 vacancy by appointment of a qualified person who shall serve for the same period
12 as if otherwise appointed.
13 (7) No vacancy by reason of voluntary resignation in the office of mayor or on a
14 legislative body shall occur unless a written resignation which specifies a
15 resignation date is tendered to the legislative body. The resignation may be
16 submitted through electronic mail if it originates from the official's electronic mail
17 address and includes also the official's handwritten signature. The resignation shall
18 be effective at the next regular or special meeting of the city legislative body
19 occurring on or after the date specified in the written letter of resignation. If a
20 resignation date is not specified, the written resignation shall be deemed to become
21 effective at the first regular or special meeting of the legislative body occurring on
22 or after its receipt.
23 (8) Pursuant to KRS 118.305(7), if a vacancy occurs which is required by law to be
24 filled temporarily by appointment, the legislative body or the Governor, whichever
25 is designated to make the appointment, shall immediately notify in writing both the
26 county clerk and the Secretary of State of the vacancy.
27 (9) Except in cities of the first class, any elected officer, in case of misconduct,
