18 Section 13. Whereas, it is critically important to protect the integrity and
19 reliability of the electoral process in order to safeguard the fundamental right to vote, and
20 it is a reasonable legislative task to seek improvement, modernization, and transparency
21 in campaign finance and election procedures without undue delay in notice to the people
22 of the Commonwealth and its election officials tasked with administering the election
23 laws within this state, an emergency is declared to exist, and this Act takes effect upon its
